COMPLETION SIGNAL
When all tests pass (Condition A), signal completion: 
CODE  444CHARS
CRITICAL - Completion requires a delivery commit: 
When all tests pass, DO NOT create a milestone. Instead: 
Stage changes for delivery commit: 
`bash git add . git diff --cached --name-only  Verify staged files ` 
Create delivery commit using commit-msg skill: Purpose: delivery (NOT milestone) No --no-verify flag (normal pre-commit hooks run) All tests must pass for commit to succeed Commit message has NO [milestone] tag 
Delivery commit distinguishes completed work from checkpoints: Milestone commits = intermediate checkpoints with incomplete tests Delivery commits = completed work with all tests passing Only delivery commits should be merged to main branch 
